    "period": "Royal Kingdom",
    "reading_one": "1 Samuel 18-19",
    "reading_two": "",
    "psalm_proverb": "Psalm 59",
    "summary": "David's victories win him the people's love and a deep friendship with Jonathan, but Saul's jealousy festers into murderous rage. Twice Saul tries to kill David, and Michal helps him escape into the night. Envy begins to consume the king while God's hand protects David.",
    "think_about_question": "Saul let jealousy of David poison his heart. When you notice envy rising over someone else's gifts or success, how can you bring it to God instead of feeding it?",
    "daily_prayer": "Lord Jesus, You know my struggles and my joys. Walk beside me today, and help me to follow You a little more closely than yesterday. Amen.",
    "quote": ""
